                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect3" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.3 Course technology requirements
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            <Run>
                                Access to an internet connection and a standard, modern web browser are the only necessary requirements of the course. 
                                If you are using an old or outdated browser, such as Internet Explorer, you may need to update. We recommend
                            </Run>
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="GoogleChromeLink" 
                                       NavigateUri="https://www.google.com/chrome/" 
                                       RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" >
                                Google Chrome.
                            </Hyperlink>

                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect4" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.4 Course duration and general time expectations
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                                It is estimated that reading fully the course material and successfully completing all graded and non-graded assignments will require approximately 120 hours in total. The time required may vary depending on the individual’s pace and environment.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            The course section with the greatest time variable to complete is the final assignment: the lesson plan. This is because feedback might be given and revisions are often necessary.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect5" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.5 How to begin and progress through the course
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Follow the program in numeric order, from module one to the final exam and lesson plan assignment.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect6" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}" >
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.6 Non-graded module self-assessment tests
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph >
                            Each module will conclude with a non-graded sell-assessment test. You can take the tests as many times as you want. 
                            Your results will be stored on your
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="ProfilePageLink" Click="ProfilePageLink_Click">Profile Page</Hyperlink>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect7" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.7 Graded exam
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            After module 4 there is a graded online exam. The exam consists of 50 multiple choice questions, each worth 2 points. A combined score of 70 is required to pass the exam.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            After submitting the exam, your score will be saved and you will be notified if you passed or not.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect8" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.8 Lesson plan assignment
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Following the 4th and final module there will be a lesson plan assignment issued as a template in .doc format. The template can be downloaded in 
                            the <Hyperlink x:Name="LessonPlanLink" Click="LessonPlanLink_Click">Lesson Plan Assignment section</Hyperlink> .
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            When you finish, submit the lesson plan in the Lesson Plan Assigment section.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            If there are no necessary corrections to be made, you will be notified that you have passed. If there are corrections needed, then you will be made aware of this.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect9" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.9 How to pass the course
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Complete all non-graded self-assessments, pass the final exam with a score of at least 70%, and complete the lesson plan exercise, preferably in that order, and that would conclude the course.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect10" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.10 Can the course be retaken if initially failed?
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Absolutely! We are here to help you succeed as a professional English teacher. The crucial point is that all TEFL certification holders successfully comprehend the knowledge required to earn the credential. The time it takes the teacher successfully complete the course is of less concern.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            The North American TEFL Academy will never deny a teacher their well-earned certification, but we will not grant the certification to anyone who has not passed the course requirements listed in section 1.1.9.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod1part1sect11" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            1.1.11 How to receive the certificate
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            You will recieve a digital certificate to your email inbox upon completion of the course. You will also be assigned a TEFL certificate code which can be accessed and verified via
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://www.echinacareers.com/" RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate">eChinaCareers TEFL Verify</Hyperlink>. Potential employers can also use this page to verify the validity of your qualification.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            If you are based in the United States or Canada you will also automatically receive a physical certification shipped to the address in your Teacher Bay profile. If you would like us to post to a different address, please contact us prior to your conclusion of the course.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            If you live outside of the United States or Canada and require a physical copy, we are willing to ship internationally at an additional expense. Please inquire further.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            All physical and digital certifications are processed on the Friday, or in the event of a holiday the following weekday, after your course was successfully completely and will be shipped out or emailed on that day. Rush delivery is available at an additional expense.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

